715
01:13:44,174 --> 01:13:46,413
We've enjoyed ourselves.

716
01:13:46,493 --> 01:13:49,532
I like a little opposition.
It clears the mind.

717
01:13:56,770 --> 01:14:01,449
So, um, I gather
you're a boxer, Mr Devlin.

718
01:14:01,528 --> 01:14:04,448
Yes, I used to do a bit
of boxing myself, actually.

719
01:14:04,528 --> 01:14:06,887
Quite a keen pugilist in one's day.

720
01:14:06,967 --> 01:14:12,125
Lost a huge part of this tooth from
a great haymaker someone gave me.

721
01:14:12,205 --> 01:14:16,524
I expect you've got some
pretty bad scabs to show as well.

722
01:14:17,483 --> 01:14:22,642
Apart, obviously, from the...
eye thing, which is beastly.

723
01:14:27,720 --> 01:14:30,079
Well, unfortunately,
during his last fight,

724
01:14:30,159 --> 01:14:33,238
Mr Devlin was gasping for air
with his tongue hanging out

725
01:14:33,318 --> 01:14:37,117
and he got this enormous uppercut
under his chin and lost most of it.

726
01:14:37,197 --> 01:14:39,876
Bulldust, Norman.

727
01:14:40,756 --> 01:14:43,675
He makes a brilliant Ulysses, anyhow.

728
01:14:43,755 --> 01:14:46,914
We always call him into the water
and he never comes.

729
01:14:46,994 --> 01:14:49,593
Whoever he was,
you'd try to get him in.

730
01:14:49,673 --> 01:14:53,671
- You'd get in the whole army.
- God, you're charming tonight.

731
01:14:53,751 --> 01:14:58,110
Thinking about the Atlantis series,
I'd like to do more research.

732
01:14:58,190 --> 01:15:01,509
I was thinking of mounting
an expedition to go and find it.

733
01:15:01,589 --> 01:15:04,028
You might like to come.

734
01:15:05,308 --> 01:15:09,666
- Devlin could be the pilot.
- Giddy could be the navigator.

735
01:15:10,306 --> 01:15:11,746
I'm not going if they're going.

736
01:15:11,825 --> 01:15:13,225
- What?
- Why not?

737
01:15:13,305 --> 01:15:15,544
I can't trust you
as far as I could kick you.

738
01:15:15,624 --> 01:15:20,103
- Thanks very much.
- What are you talking about?

739
01:15:20,183 --> 01:15:21,622
You know!

740
01:15:21,702 --> 01:15:24,821
You always eat cheese
when you're feeling guilty.

741
01:15:25,421 --> 01:15:26,861
Excuse me.

742
01:15:29,620 --> 01:15:32,619
Sorry, I'd better go and see
if she's all right.

743
01:15:36,897 --> 01:15:40,816
- What?
- Nothing.

744
01:15:44,935 --> 01:15:46,774
Piglet? You all right?

745
01:15:46,854 --> 01:15:49,253
Yes, I'm... I'm fine, thank you.

746
01:15:50,973 --> 01:15:53,372
Are you feeling a bit funny?

747
01:15:54,452 --> 01:15:56,011
Probably all that Stilton.

748
01:15:57,690 --> 01:16:00,849
You were packing it down,
weren't you?

749
01:16:05,288 --> 01:16:08,207
- Well, I'd better... I'll go back.
- Pooh.

750
01:16:10,206 --> 01:16:13,085
I think... we should talk.

751
01:16:14,885 --> 01:16:20,723
- Right you are. What about?
- Ever since we got here, I...

752
01:16:23,482 --> 01:16:26,841
Well, now, I think some things
are best left unsaid.

753
01:16:28,240 --> 01:16:31,719
But that means
we'll always be strangers.

754
01:16:31,799 --> 01:16:33,999
No, not really.

755
01:16:35,798 --> 01:16:38,757
- Only small parts of us.
- The bad parts.

756
01:16:39,837 --> 01:16:42,596
No, I think it's good
to have a few secrets.

757
01:16:44,955 --> 01:16:46,874
Do you?

758
01:16:50,033 --> 01:16:51,833
That way, in 50 years' time,

759
01:16:51,913 --> 01:16:55,552
we'll still be able
to surprise each other.

760
01:16:56,471 --> 01:16:58,111
Perhaps you're right.

761
01:17:04,589 --> 01:17:06,548
I love you, Piglet.

762
01:17:38,218 --> 01:17:41,377
- What's the matter?
- You must've been dreaming.

763
01:17:41,457 --> 01:17:43,296
When you saw someone with Devlin.

764
01:17:43,376 --> 01:17:45,295
You were so drunk.

765
01:17:45,375 --> 01:17:48,894
I looked in here
and you were absolutely sozzled.

766
01:17:48,974 --> 01:17:52,693
- But it was so real.
- Dreams always are.

767
01:17:53,413 --> 01:17:55,972
The other two swear it wasn't them

768
01:17:56,052 --> 01:17:58,291
and you know how they like to boast.

769
01:17:59,571 --> 01:18:01,850
Do you still like him?

770
01:18:03,009 --> 01:18:07,768
- I suppose so.
- You should go in and see him, then.

771
01:18:07,848 --> 01:18:09,007
Now?

772
01:18:09,087 --> 01:18:13,206
That's what your dream
was telling you.

773
01:18:14,526 --> 01:18:17,685
Here, put this on.

774
01:18:17,765 --> 01:18:20,844
- But it's your wedding ring.
- It's always brought me luck.

775
01:18:20,924 --> 01:18:23,403
- Has it?
- Always.

776
01:18:23,483 --> 01:18:25,282
Wear these.

777
01:18:28,281 --> 01:18:30,241
Try some of this.

778
01:18:35,479 --> 01:18:38,198
We'll have to fix your hair.

779
01:18:52,713 --> 01:18:54,473
Good luck.

780
01:22:01,531 --> 01:22:04,290
I want to wake up now.

781
01:22:17,606 --> 01:22:21,485
- What? It was night...
- You were shouting.

782
01:22:21,565 --> 01:22:24,244
Really loudly.
I heard you from the garden.

783
01:22:24,324 --> 01:22:28,163
But I wanted to tell you about
last night. Oh, it was wonderful.

784
01:22:28,243 --> 01:22:31,522
I mean, I didn't do everything
with him because...

785
01:22:31,602 --> 01:22:34,241
I don't think
he's good enough for me but...

786
01:22:34,321 --> 01:22:37,680
oh, he did some things
which were just...

787
01:22:39,919 --> 01:22:41,358
Gosh!

788
01:22:49,716 --> 01:22:52,595
How dare you use her
without permission?

789
01:22:52,675 --> 01:22:57,233
- I don't need permission.
- It infers that she modelled!

790
01:22:58,353 --> 01:23:00,552
You cannot just put
someone in your painting!

791
01:23:00,632 --> 01:23:04,151
It's totally compromising.
She'll be outraged. I'm outraged!

792
01:23:04,231 --> 01:23:07,630
- Perhaps we ought to ask her.
- I don't need to. If she wanted...

793
01:23:07,710 --> 01:23:10,029
Anthony? What's the matter?

794
01:23:10,109 --> 01:23:13,108
Mr Lindsay has put you
in his latest painting.

795
01:23:14,428 --> 01:23:17,067
He has to paint over you
or we'll take legal action.

796
01:23:17,147 --> 01:23:21,185
He can turn you into someone else.
You'd better have a look.

797
01:23:46,137 --> 01:23:48,176
Well?

798
01:24:10,649 --> 01:24:13,248
It's a good likeness.

799
01:24:50,236 --> 01:24:55,035
Devlin, better get back
to work. Catch.

800
01:26:00,573 --> 01:26:03,212
They're asleep.

801
01:26:03,292 --> 01:26:05,252
For goodness sake!

802
01:26:09,730 --> 01:26:11,130
We'll be arrested.

803
01:26:14,888 --> 01:26:17,488
We'll be excommunicated.

